verbose_text: The objective of the present study was to assess the usefulness of the plasma levels of mid-regional proadrenomedullin (MR-proADM) and mid-regional proatrial natriuretic peptide (MR-proANP) in differentiating pneumonia from other lower respiratory tract infections (LRTIs).
evidence: levels of mid-regional proadrenomedullin (MR-proADM) and mid-regional proatrial natriuretic peptide
